Add turmeric and salt. Mix well. Cover and rest in the fridge for 30 minutes.<br \\\/>Place onion, garlic, ginger, coriander leaves and chilli in the jug of a blender with 1 cup of water. Process until smooth. Set aside.<br \\\/>In a large heavy bottomed saucepan or cast iron casserole, heat ghee on high. Add cinnamon, bay leaf, coriander seeds, fennel seeds and black cardamom. Saut\\u00e9 for a few seconds. Add the marinated meat and potatoes. Saut\\u00e9 for a few minutes, tossing occasionally until meat is sealed on the outside and starting to brown. Add the onion mixture and reduce heat to medium.<\\\/p><p>Add cumin, garam masala and tomatoes. Season with salt to taste. Cover and simmer on medium for 40 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Add coconut milk. Cover and simmer for a further 15 minutes. Serve hot with steamed rice.<\\\/p>\",\"animation_group\":{\"selected\":\"no\",\"yes\":{\"animation\":{\"animation\":\"fadeInUp\",\"delay\":\"200\"}}},\"responsive\":{\"desktop_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_landscape_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"smartphone_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"}},\"class\":\"\"}}]}]}]"}}}

Add turmeric and salt. Mix well. Cover and rest in the fridge for 30 minutes.<br \\\/>Place onion, garlic, ginger, coriander leaves and chilli in the jug of a blender with 1 cup of water. Process until smooth. Set aside.<br \\\/>In a large heavy bottomed saucepan or cast iron casserole, heat ghee on high. Add cinnamon, bay leaf, coriander seeds, fennel seeds and black cardamom. Saut\\u00e9 for a few seconds. Add the marinated meat and potatoes. Saut\\u00e9 for a few minutes, tossing occasionally until meat is sealed on the outside and starting to brown. Add the onion mixture and reduce heat to medium.<\\\/p><p>Add cumin, garam masala and tomatoes. Season with salt to taste. Cover and simmer on medium for 40 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Add coconut milk. Cover and simmer for a further 15 minutes. Serve hot with steamed rice.<\\\/p>\",\"animation_group\":{\"selected\":\"no\",\"yes\":{\"animation\":{\"animation\":\"fadeInUp\",\"delay\":\"200\"}}},\"responsive\":{\"desktop_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_landscape_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"smartphone_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"}},\"class\":\"\"}}]}]}]"}}}

Add turmeric and salt. Mix well. Cover and rest in the fridge for 30 minutes.<br \\\/>Place onion, garlic, ginger, coriander leaves and chilli in the jug of a blender with 1 cup of water. Process until smooth. Set aside.<br \\\/>In a large heavy bottomed saucepan or cast iron casserole, heat ghee on high. Add cinnamon, bay leaf, coriander seeds, fennel seeds and black cardamom. Saut\\u00e9 for a few seconds. Add the marinated meat and potatoes. Saut\\u00e9 for a few minutes, tossing occasionally until meat is sealed on the outside and starting to brown. Add the onion mixture and reduce heat to medium.<\\\/p><p>Add cumin, garam masala and tomatoes. Season with salt to taste. Cover and simmer on medium for 40 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Add coconut milk. Cover and simmer for a further 15 minutes. Serve hot with steamed rice.<\\\/p>\",\"animation_group\":{\"selected\":\"no\",\"yes\":{\"animation\":{\"animation\":\"fadeInUp\",\"delay\":\"200\"}}},\"responsive\":{\"desktop_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_landscape_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"smartphone_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"}},\"class\":\"\"}}]}]}]"}}}

Add turmeric and salt. Mix well. Cover and rest in the fridge for 30 minutes.<br \\\/>Place onion, garlic, ginger, coriander leaves and chilli in the jug of a blender with 1 cup of water. Process until smooth. Set aside.<br \\\/>In a large heavy bottomed saucepan or cast iron casserole, heat ghee on high. Add cinnamon, bay leaf, coriander seeds, fennel seeds and black cardamom. Saut\\u00e9 for a few seconds. Add the marinated meat and potatoes. Saut\\u00e9 for a few minutes, tossing occasionally until meat is sealed on the outside and starting to brown. Add the onion mixture and reduce heat to medium.<\\\/p><p>Add cumin, garam masala and tomatoes. Season with salt to taste. Cover and simmer on medium for 40 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Add coconut milk. Cover and simmer for a further 15 minutes. Serve hot with steamed rice.<\\\/p>\",\"animation_group\":{\"selected\":\"no\",\"yes\":{\"animation\":{\"animation\":\"fadeInUp\",\"delay\":\"200\"}}},\"responsive\":{\"desktop_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_landscape_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"tablet_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"},\"smartphone_display\":{\"selected\":\"yes\"}},\"class\":\"\"}}]}]}]"}}}

Add turmeric and salt. Mix well. Cover and rest in the fridge for 30 minutes.<br \\\/>Place onion, garlic, ginger, coriander leaves and chilli in the jug of a blender with 1 cup of water. Process until smooth. Set aside.<br \\\/>In a large heavy bottomed saucepan or cast iron casserole, heat ghee on high. Add cinnamon, bay leaf, coriander seeds, fennel seeds and black cardamom. Saut\\u00e9 for a few seconds. Add the marinated meat and potatoes. Saut\\u00e9 for a few minutes, tossing occasionally until meat is sealed on the outside and starting to brown. Add the onion mixture and reduce heat to medium.<\\\/p><p>Add cumin, garam masala and tomatoes. Season with salt to taste. Cover and simmer on medium for 40 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Add coconut milk. Cover and simmer for a further 15 minutes.
